# Six ARAF Dimensions

ARAF assesses governance posture across six dimensions. Each dimension captures a distinct category of governance risk. Together they produce a composite picture of the governance architecture of an autonomous system deployment.

A classification without a dimensional profile has produced a score. A classification with a dimensional profile has produced governance infrastructure: the information that allows remediation to be targeted, governance investment to be prioritised, and institutional audiences to understand where governance strength and weakness sit.

